	<article id="post-566" class="post-566 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-knetwork category-networks-of-the-future category-news category-research">
		<header class="entry-header">
						<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="http://blogs.oii.ox.ac.uk/cobo/?p=566" rel="bookmark">KNetworks Competition: Networks of Regional Innovation</a></h1>
			
						<div class="entry-meta">
				<span class="sep">Posted on </span><a href="http://blogs.oii.ox.ac.uk/cobo/?p=566" title="4:11 pm" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2012-08-28T16:11:10+00:00">28/08/2012</time></a><span class="by-author"> <span class="sep"> by </span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://blogs.oii.ox.ac.uk/cobo/?author=2" title="View all posts by Cristobal Cobo" rel="author">Cristobal Cobo</a></span></span>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
			
						<div class="comments-link">
				<a href="http://blogs.oii.ox.ac.uk/cobo/?p=566#comments">1</a>			</div>
					</header><!-- .entry-header -->

				<div class="entry-content">
			<p><a title="Post-it por danicuki, en Flickr" href="http://www.knetworks.eu/"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://farm7.staticflickr.com/6180/6137367539_9e556734aa_z.jpg" alt="Post-it" width="427" height="640" /></a><br />
At the Oxford Internet Institute we are pleased to announce a competition for the most innovative web-based platform enabling regional networks of innovation for public, private or research organizations.</p>
<p>The platforms should foster innovation in the three areas of knowledge transfer; tourism; or e-government – broadly conceived. They should be particularly relevant to the Atlantic Area (<a href="http://ec.europa.eu/regional_policy/country/prordn/details_new.cfm?gv_PAY=UK&amp;gv_reg=520&amp;gv_PGM=1256&amp;gv_defL=4&amp;LAN=7">link</a>), but again this should be interpreted in a wide and inclusive sense.</p>
<p>Candidate organizations will need to submit an online profile/form explaining why they deserve the award). Entries will be judged by a panel of experts and by popular vote. The top three entries will receive a <strong>5,000 EUR</strong> prize for their institution. <strong>The deadline to participate in this competition will be the 29th of October 2012. More information here: <a href="http://www.knetworks.eu/">http://www.knetworks.eu/</a></strong></p>
					</div><!-- .entry-content -->
		
